+### [3]
+
+# Scope of the Work
+
+**Task 1**: Model the fault mode and call chain of the scheduling management and control system for large-scale complex systems.
+
+**Objectives**:
+1. Model restart faults, performance deterioration faults, and multi-point faults based on the physical failure mechanism and statistical analysis, estimate the probability distribution of different faults.
+2. Parse and model the entire process path of the request in the system by analyzing the software stack of the management, control, and scheduling engine.
+
+**Task 2**: Evaluate the dynamic availability of system management, control, and scheduling, support load scenario analysis such as inference in typical large EP scenarios and agent multi-agent, analyze the sensitivity of each component, and locate the cluster availability bottleneck.
+
+**Objective**:
