+### [6]
+
+# Overview of LLM based Multi-Agents
+
+The **LLM-based multi-agent system** consists of specialized **agents** with different **roles**. Some of the agents may use single-agents or leverage external tools to fulfill their *Service Level Objectives* (**SLO**), but the overall behavior of the system is determined by communication, orchestration and the quality of the model. According to the *common surveys*$^{[1]}$, errors and performance degradations can propagate between agents leading to the *Cascading effects* and *logical errors*.
+
+We considered several multi-agent systems like **Codex**$^{[2]}$, **OpenManus**$^{[3]}$ and **CrewAI**$^{[4]}$, that demonstrate the transition from using LLM as a single model to agent-based systems in which LLM acts as an active component, performing actions, interacting with the environment and other agents:
+
+| Tool | Remarkable features |
+| :--- | :--- |
+| Codex | • Autonomous LLM agent<br>• Possibility of considering long-term and parallel tasks |
+| OpenManus | • Integration of external tools and APIs<br>• Well-illustrates dependency errors |
+| CrewAI | • Explicit agent orchestration<br>• Deterministic/LLM-based logic capability<br>• Convenient for scenarios and experiments |
+
+All these multi-agent systems are **open-source** and thus **easy to research**. Yet, these systems essentially have a **focus on functionality**, not reliability (fault handling only done on lower abstraction levels). Thus, there is **no availability analysis** done for these systems so as **no ready-to-use fault-models** and sub-health benchmarks.
+
+### [7]
+
+# Multi-agent system design
+
+While having various targets, the top-level architecture of all the multi-agent system are pretty-similar and consists of the following major parts:
+
+*   **User Interface** - user entry point: task formulation and file upload.
+*   **Coordination Layer** - central control module of the system
+*   **Task Assignment & Dataflow** - mechanism for distributing subtasks and controlling the flow of execution.
+*   **Specialized Agents** - performers of specific types of operations
+*   **Execution & Combination** - Aggregation of intermediate results and formation of a single answer.
+*   **Output** - the final result of the system's operation
+
+> 📊 **FIGURE**: Manus/OpenManus$^{[3]}$ conceptual architecture and workflow$^{[5]}$.
+>
+> **Визуальный анализ**:
+> - **Тип**: Схема архитектуры системы (System Architecture and Workflow).
+> - **Основные блоки**:
+>     - **User Interface**: Включает модули "Chat" и "File Upload".
+>     - **Manus Coordination Layer**: Содержит компоненты "Memory/Knowledge", "Task Decomposition" и "Agent Orchestration".
+>     - **Task Assignment & Dataflow**: Промежуточный слой распределения задач.
+>     - **Слой агентов (Specialized Agents)**: Представлен четырьмя типами: Agent (Web) для браузинга и экстракции, Agent (Data) для анализа и API доступа, Agent (Code) для Python и автоматизации, Agent (Files) для менеджмента и процессинга.
+>     - **Execution & Combination**: Блок выполнения, где агенты могут взаимодействовать и обмениваться данными.
+>     - **Output (Examples)**: Примеры выходных данных — Reports, Charts, Websites, Spreadsheets, Notifications.
+> - **Ключевой тренд**: Демонстрируется линейно-циклический процесс от ввода пользователя через координацию и специализированных агентов к формированию комбинированного результата.
+
+### [8]
+
+# Example: graph-based Model of OpenManus
+
+The system can be viewed as a $2$-layer tree structure: orchestrator on the top-layer and all dependent/orchestrated agents on the $2^{nd}$ layer.
+
+> 📊 **FIGURE**: Execution flow of OpenManus (author's diagram)
+>
+> **Визуальный анализ**:
+> - **Тип**: Иерархический направленный граф (блок-схема архитектуры).
+> - **Уровни**: 
+>   1. **User** (входная точка).
+>   2. **User Interface**.
+>   3. **Coordination Layer (Orchestrator)** — центральный узел управления.
+>   4. **Agent Layer**: Web Agent, Data Agent, Code Agent, Files Agent, Execution & Combination.
+>   5. **Resource/Output Layer**: Web/APIs, Data Sources/APIs, Python Environment, File System, Final Output.
+> - **Связи**: Двунаправленные стрелки между оркестратором, агентами и их соответствующими средами исполнения, что указывает на циклы обратной связи.
+> - **Ключевой тренд**: Демонстрация централизованного управления (orchestration), где координатор распределяет задачи между специализированными агентами.
+
+The architecture model of ***OpenManus*** is a good example:
+
+**Nodes** reflect orchestrator, agents, tools, aggregation, etc.
+
+**Edges** show the interaction: *orchestrator assigns a step*, then *agent calls a tool* and finally *result is returned back* (typical feedback loop).
+
+**Feedbacks** reflect retracements that increase latency and can lead to quality degradation.
+
+**Nodes/edges** can be described by specifying the probability of failure, the number of retries and quantifying the contribution of components and the risk of SLA violation.
+
+**The management of data flows in the system is handled by an orchestrator**, *but control & scheduling are handled by lower system layers.*
