+# Stochastic simulation: Ready-to-use approaches
+
+*APEX+*$^{[22]}$ - this is an LLM serving (inference system) simulator that allows you to simulate the processing of a request flow and quantitatively evaluate performance and SLO compliance without fully deploying a production cluster.
+
+**Usage:**
+*   Simulates query execution over time, including trace-driven scenarios (realistic query sequences).
+*   Models the effects of batching, queuing, and parallel execution that directly impact latency and throughput.
+*   Calculates key user experience metrics: $TTFT$ - time to first token, $TPOT$ - time per token.
+*   Allows you to compare different execution plans/configurations and evaluate what proportion of requests fit within the specified SLOs according to $TTFT/TPOT$.
+*   Can rely on hardware/operation performance profiles to bring simulation closer to real GPU platforms.
+
+**Restrictions:**
+*   Focus on performance/SLO; complex failure scenarios (correlated incidents, cascading component degradations) usually require adding a fault model on top of the simulator.
+*   Some external factors (e.g. network effects) can be taken into account in a simplified manner.
